INSERT INTO title (title_id, title, subtitle, imageurl, imagesource, date, readtime, content, tag) VALUES
(51,"The ominous forces driving bitcoin's plunge", "subtitle", "https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/aa06f222-a18c-4b2f-8224-92fc220e00ec/image.png","","2023-08-22",3," <tbody><tr><td class='dd' align='left' style='padding:0px 0px;text-align:left;word-break:break-word;'><p><span style=''>Are you familiar with this graph? Itâ€™s an anatomy of a typical bubble, applicable to almost any investment asset. Pay attention to the four stages of investors </span></p></td></tr><tr><td style='padding-bottom:27px;padding-left:18px;padding-right:18px;padding-top:0px;' class='ee'><div style='margin-left:0px;' class='edm_outlooklist'><ol start='1' style='list-style-type:decimal;margin:0px 0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 0px;'><li class='listItem ultext'><p style='padding:0px;text-align:left;word-break:break-word;'><span style=''><b>Smart Money:</b></span><span style=''> Astute and knowledgeable investors enter the scene. Prices remain relatively stable during this period.</span></p></li><li class='listItem ultext'><p style='padding:0px;text-align:left;word-break:break-word;'><span style=''><b>Institutional Investors:</b></span><span style=''> Price starts to rise, and media coverage increases. At this time, institutional investors temporarily create a bear trap for additional purchases.</span></p></li><li class='listItem ultext'><p style='padding:0px;text-align:left;word-break:break-word;'><span style=''><b>The General Public: </b></span><span style=''>Involvement of the general populace, with media coverage gaining further traction. There is a significant price increase. </span><span style=''><span style='text-decoration:underline;'>Institutional investors and smart money begin to cash out their holdings at this phase.</span></span></p></li><li class='listItem ultext'><p style='padding:0px;text-align:left;word-break:break-word;'><span style=''><b>Market Contraction:</b></span><span style=''> As a consequence of the widespread public involvement, the availability of willing buyers at high price levels dwindles. Consequently, prices experience a sharp drop as the general public sells off their holdings.</span></p></li></ol></div></td></tr><tr><td class='dd' align='left' style='padding:0px 0px;text-align:left;word-break:break-word;'><p><span style=''>Now, notice the similarities with bitcoinâ€™s graph from 2019 to 2022.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td align='center' valign='top' style='padding: 12px 0px 12px; ' class='dd'><table role='none' border='0' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='0' style='margin:0 auto 0 auto;'><tbody><tr><td align='center' valign='top' style='width:626px;'><img src='https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/c2a1ae5f-7ebb-46e5-9662-759b820fa68e/image.png' alt='' height='auto' width='626' style='display:block;width:100%;' border='0'></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td style='padding-bottom:27px;padding-left:18px;padding-right:18px;padding-top:0px;' class='ee'><div style='margin-left:0px;' class='edm_outlooklist'><ol start='1' style='list-style-type:decimal;margin:0px 0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 0px;'><li class='listItem ultext'><p style='padding:0px;text-align:left;word-break:break-word;'><span style=''><b>2019: </b></span><span style=''>Smart Money</span></p></li><li class='listItem ultext'><p style='padding:0px;text-align:left;word-break:break-word;'><span style=''><b>2020: </b></span><span style=''>Institutional Investors</span></p></li><li class='listItem ultext'><p style='padding:0px;text-align:left;word-break:break-word;'><span style=''><b>2021: </b></span><span style=''>The General Public</span></p></li><li class='listItem ultext'><p style='padding:0px;text-align:left;word-break:break-word;'><span style=''><b>2022: </b></span><span style=''>Market Contraction</span></p></li></ol></div></td></tr><tr><td class='dd' align='left' style='padding:0px 0px;text-align:left;word-break:break-word;'><p><span style=''>After the end of a cycle last year, bitcoin appears to be re-entering its Smart Money/Institutional phase, especially given notable moves like BlackRock filing for a Bitcoin ETF.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td class='dd' align='start' style='padding:0px 0px;text-align:start;word-break:break-word;'><p><span style=''><b>Last week's downturn</b></span><span style=''> in bitcoinâ€™s price seems to fit the classic profile of a 'bear trap', likely set by institutional investors. Importantly, rumors about SpaceX selling its bitcoin holdings have been debunked. Be cautious and don't fall prey to media narratives that could be part of larger strategic moves.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td class='dd' align='start' style='padding:0px 0px;text-align:start;word-break:break-word;'><p><span style=''><b>Looking ahead to 2024,</b></span><span style=''> expectations point to the next phase of the cycle: mass adoption by the general public. This could significantly shift market dynamics to the upside.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td class='dd' align='start' style='padding:0px 0px;text-align:start;word-break:break-word;'><p><span style=''>However, it's essential to remember that this is just one predictive model among many. Always consider it within the context of a more diversified investment strategy.</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody>", "BITCOIN");
